.TH REMOTE\-SETUP 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
remote\-setup.sh \- run machine-setup on remote machines via SSH
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B remote\-setup.sh
\fIUSER@HOST\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Connects to a remote machine over SSH, copies or clones the machine-setup
repository, and runs \fBsetup.sh\fR with the specified options. Any options
not consumed by \fBremote\-setup.sh\fR are passed through to \fBsetup.sh\fR
on the remote host.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile to use on the remote machine.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Pass \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR to the remote \fBsetup.sh\fR invocation.
.PP
All other options are forwarded to \fBsetup.sh\fR on the remote host
(e.g., \fB\-\-no\-packages\fR, \fB\-\-no\-dotfiles\fR).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (SSH connection failure, remote setup failure).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run full setup on a remote machine:
.B remote\-setup.sh user@web.example.com \-\-profile full
.TP
Preview changes on a remote machine:
.B remote\-setup.sh user@server.local \-\-dry\-run
.TP
Skip packages on the remote host:
.B remote\-setup.sh user@host \-\-profile minimal \-\-no\-packages
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1),
.BR fleet\-manager.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
